<h1 id="temporaneo">Temporaneo</h1>
<h2 id="roadmap">Roadmap</h2>
<h3 id="objectives">Objectives</h3>
<p>This research aims to investigate over a coherent way to extract geographical information in the narrative storytelling of Decameron 2nd day novelle by the perspective of the narration (extra-diegetic / fabula).</p>
<h3 id="pipeline">Pipeline</h3>
<p>Preliminary steps * <span>[</span>DONE<span>]</span> Collect the corpus in a textual form (e.g. liberliber) * <span>[</span>DONE<span>]</span> Clean the corpus * <span>[</span>DONE<span>]</span> Divide the corpus into partials (e.g. 0207.txt, 0203.txt namefile: NNnn.txt where NN=02) * Tools testing * <span>[</span>DONE<span>]</span> POS and Lemmatization correctness rate =&gt; UDPIPE wins</p>
<h3 id="geographic-information">Geographic information</h3>
<ul>
<li><p><span>[</span>DONE<span>]</span> Use UDPIPE with the 10 subcorpora. Write the relative CONLL-U files of each partials</p></li>
<li><p><span>[</span>DONE<span>]</span> Extract all the PROPN SP tokens for each partials</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Using R</p>
<pre><code>    infile &lt;- read.csv(CONNLU)
    df &lt;- infile[infile[,4] == &quot;PROPN&quot;, ]
    write.csv(df, outfile)</code></pre>
